properties.headline: Flood Warning issued February 2 at 1:57AM PST until February 2 at 9:02AM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
...The Flood Warning has ended for the following rivers in
Washington...

Satsop River Near Satsop affecting Grays Harbor County
Skagit River Near Concrete affecting Skagit County
Skykomish River Near Gold Bar affecting Snohomish County
Tolt River Above Carnation affecting King County
Cowlitz River At Randle affecting Lewis County

...The Flood Warning continues for the following rivers in
Washington...

Skagit River Near Mt. Vernon affecting Skagit County
Snohomish River Near Monroe affecting Snohomish County
Snohomish River At Snohomish affecting Snohomish County
White River 10 N R Street Bridge affecting King and Pierce Counties
Skokomish River At Potlatch affecting Mason County
Snoqualmie River Near Snoqualmie Falls affecting King County

Showers will decrease today. Hydrologically significant
precipitation is not expected for the next couple of days.

The Flood Warning continues for
The Snoqualmie River Near Snoqualmie Falls
* Until this morning.
* At  1:15 AM Sunday the flow was 19059 cfs.
* Flood flow is 20000 cfs.
* Fell below flood flow early this morning.
* No additional flooding is forecast.
* Impact...At 12000 cfs, the Snoqualmie River will spill over its
banks between the town of Snoqualmie and Fall City...covering
pasture lands and several roads along the river. This river level
on the Snoqualmie corresponds roughly to a phase 2 flood in the
King County flood system.
properties.instruction:
Do not drive cars...vans...or trucks through flooded areas...this is
the cause of most flood related deaths in Washington. Be alert for
rapid changes and monitor developments by listening to NOAA Weather
radio or other local media.
